{{Quote|They signed on under General Antilles. If they had paid attention to him, most if not all of them would still be alive. If you want to know who betrayed your people to death, look to the commander who broke ranks.|[[Jagged Fel]], to [[Lensi]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy]]''</ref>}}
'''Duro Squadron''' was an all-[[Duros/Legends|Duros]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] that fought for the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. Formed after the [[Battle of Duro (Yuuzhan Vong War)|fall of Duro]], they were devoted to reclaiming their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] from the [[Extragalactic/Legends|extra-galactic]] invaders. The [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] of the squadron were a mixed group, ranging from seasoned combat veterans to those who had never before served in a military unit.

In [[29 ABY/Legends|29 ABY]], they fought to [[Battle of the Duro system|retake Duro]] under [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Yurf Col]]. The Squadron was utterly destroyed, however, when they refused to follow an order to retreat given by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]].

